      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/Search\" title=\"Search\">Search</a> * Node</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/File:Bonatti-caput_et_cauda_draconis.PNG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ca/Bonatti-caput_et_cauda_draconis.PNG/330px-Bonatti-caput_et_cauda_draconis.PNG\" width=\"300\" height=\"431\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ca/Bonatti-caput_et_cauda_draconis.PNG/500px-Bonatti-caput_et_cauda_draconis.PNG 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/ca/Bonatti-caput_et_cauda_draconis.PNG 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:Bonatti-caput_et_cauda_draconis.PNG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The Dragon's Head and Tail <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Node</b>, (<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vertex_%28graph_theory%29\">vertex</a>)<br />\nthe fundamental unit in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graph_theory\">graph theory</a> and, applied to <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computer_science\">computer science</a>, basic unit to structure and link devices of a <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computer_network\">network</a> as well as <a href=\"/Data\" title=\"Data\">data</a>, such as items of a <a href=\"/Linked_List\" title=\"Linked List\">linked list</a> or <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tree_%28data_structure%29\">tree structure</a>. This page is about the <b>node</b> of the <a href=\"/Search_Tree\" title=\"Search Tree\">search tree</a> in the game of chess, which represents the alternating white and black to move <a href=\"/Chess_Position\" title=\"Chess Position\">positions</a> and keeps its state dependent on the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tree_traversal\">tree traversal</a>. Inside a <a href=\"/Depth-First\" title=\"Depth-First\">depth-first</a> search, nodes are usually counted at top of the <a href=\"/Recursion\" title=\"Recursion\">recursive</a> search routine, i.e. for the purpose to determine <a href=\"/Nodes_per_Second\" title=\"Nodes per Second\">nodes per second</a>. The <a href=\"/Moves\" title=\"Moves\">move</a> is the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Directed_graph\">directed edge</a> which connects an ordered pair of nodes or positions.\n</p><p>Nodes are classified by their topological properties inside the search tree, and in context of <a href=\"/Alpha-Beta\" title=\"Alpha-Beta\">alpha-beta</a> and its enhancements, by their <a href=\"/Node_Types\" title=\"Node Types\">type</a> as expected in accordance to the <a href=\"/Search_Tree#MinimalGameTree\" title=\"Search Tree\">minimal tree</a> before searching this node, or as determined after searching the node. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Node_Types\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Node Types</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Topology\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Topology</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Depth\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Depth</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#1995_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1995 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#2000_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2000 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#2020_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2020 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Node_Types\">Node Types</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Node&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Node Types\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><a href=\"/Node_Types\" title=\"Node Types\">Node Types</a> of the <a href=\"/Search_Tree#MinimalGameTree\" title=\"Search Tree\">minimal tree</a> - enumerated as classified by <a href=\"/Donald_Knuth\" title=\"Donald Knuth\">Knuth</a> and Moore:\n</p>\n<ol><li> <a href=\"/Node_Types#PV\" title=\"Node Types\">PV-Node</a> Knuth's <b>Type 1</b></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Node_Types#CUT\" title=\"Node Types\">Cut-Node</a> Knuth's <b>Type 2</b>, also called <a href=\"/Fail-High\" title=\"Fail-High\">fail-high</a> node</li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Node_Types#ALL\" title=\"Node Types\">All-Node</a> Knuth's <b>Type 3</b>, also called <a href=\"/Fail-Low\" title=\"Fail-Low\">fail-low</a> node</li></ol>\n<p>PV-nodes are often treated differently by the search - see <a href=\"/Principal_Variation_Search\" title=\"Principal Variation Search\">Principal Variation Search</a> or <a href=\"/Internal_Iterative_Deepening\" title=\"Internal Iterative Deepening\">Internal Iterative Deepening</a> for examples.\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Topology\">Topology</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Node&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Topology\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Root\" title=\"Root\">Root Node</a> - depth = D</li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Leftmost_Node\" title=\"Leftmost Node\">Leftmost Node</a> - are always PV-nodes <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Sibling_Node\" title=\"Sibling Node\">Sibling Node</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Interior_Node\" title=\"Interior Node\">Interior Node</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Leaf_Node\" title=\"Leaf Node\">Leaf Node</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Terminal_Node\" title=\"Terminal Node\">Terminal Node</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Depth\">Depth</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Node&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Depth\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<table class=\"wikitable\">\n\n<tr>\n<th> Name\n</th>\n<th> Heinz\n</th>\n<th> Hyatt\n</th>\n<th> Ambiguity\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>  <a href=\"/Horizon_Node\" title=\"Horizon Node\">Horizon Node</a>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 0\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> -\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;\"> *\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>  <a href=\"/Frontier_Nodes\" title=\"Frontier Nodes\">Frontier Node</a>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 1\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 0\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;\"> *\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>  <a href=\"/Pre_Frontier_Node\" title=\"Pre Frontier Node\">Pre Frontier Node</a>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 2\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:right;\"> 1\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;\"> *\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>  <a href=\"/Quiescent_Node\" title=\"Quiescent Node\">Quiescent Node</a>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;\" colspan=\"2\"> &lt;= 0\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></table>\n<ul><li>) <i>There seems an ambiguity according to the definition of frontier versus horizon nodes.</i> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> .</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Node&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Chess_Position\" title=\"Chess Position\">Chess Position</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Nodes_per_Second\" title=\"Nodes per Second\">Nodes per Second</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Principal_Variation\" title=\"Principal Variation\">Principal Variation</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Score\" title=\"Score\">Score</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Node&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1995_...\">1995 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Node&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: 1995 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://groups.google.com/group/rec.games.chess.computer/browse_frm/thread/926eaf0869b6f176#\">quiescent vs non-quiescent node counting</a> by <a href=\"/Robert_Hyatt\" title=\"Robert Hyatt\">Robert Hyatt</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">rgcc</a>, July 01, 1996</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=14239\">Node counting confusion</a> by <a href=\"/Don_Dailey\" title=\"Don Dailey\">Don Dailey</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 17, 1998</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=20796\">Bratko-Kopec Test - Node Counts</a> by <a href=\"/Peter_McKenzie\" title=\"Peter McKenzie\">Peter McKenzie</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, June 17, 1998&#160;» <a href=\"/Bratko-Kopec_Test\" title=\"Bratko-Kopec Test\">Bratko-Kopec Test</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=55179\">nodes per ply</a> by <a href=\"/Leonid_Liberman\" title=\"Leonid Liberman\">Leonid</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, June 10, 1999</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2000_...\">2000 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Node&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: 2000 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=215421\">How to count the nodes?</a> by <a href=\"/Benny_Antonsson\" title=\"Benny Antonsson\">Benny Antonsson</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 25, 2002</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=285939\">ALL node definition </a> by <a href=\"/Alvaro_Cardoso\" title=\"Alvaro Cardoso\">Alvaro Cardoso</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 21, 2003</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=387460\">simple node definitions question</a> by Michael Henderson, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 13, 2004</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=23037\">To Jeroen and interested minds, re. Tiger node count</a> by <a href=\"/Christophe_Th%C3%A9ron\" title=\"Christophe Théron\">Christophe Théron</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 15, 2008</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010_...\">2010 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Node&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: 2010 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-chess.org/viewtopic.php?f=5&amp;t=1004\">Node counting</a> by <a href=\"/Mark_Watkins\" title=\"Mark Watkins\">BB+</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">OpenChess Forum</a>, January 20, 2011&#160;» <a href=\"/Rybka\" title=\"Rybka\">Rybka</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=40269\">How do you count nodes?</a> by <a href=\"/Edsel_Apostol\" title=\"Edsel Apostol\">Edsel Apostol</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 04, 2011</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=57033\">counting nodes vs counting evaluations</a> by <a href=\"/Ed_Schroder\" title=\"Ed Schroder\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 19, 2015</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2020_...\">2020 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Node&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Edit section: 2020 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=74399\">Counting nodes correctly</a> by Steven Griffin, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 07, 2020</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Node&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Node\">Node from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vertex_%28graph_theory%29\">Vertex (graph theory) from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Node_%28computer_science%29\">Node (computer science) from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Node_%28networking%29\">Node (networking) from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orbital_node\">Orbital node from Wikipedia</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Node&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Bonatti-caput_et_cauda_draconis.PNG\">The Dragon's Head and Tail</a> refer ascending and descending <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lunar_node\">Lunar nodes</a>, Image from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guido_Bonatti\">Guido Bonatti</a> (<b>1550</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://hardenberg.jalb.de/display_page.php?elementId=5363\">Foroliviensis Mathematici De Astronomia Tractatvs X.&#160;: Vniuersum quod iudiciariam rationem Natiuitatum, Aeris, Tempestatum, attinet, comprehendentes. Adiectus est Cl. Ptolemaei liber Fructus, cum commentarijs vtilissimis Georgij Trapezunt</a></i>. pp. 119, from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Johannes_a_Lasco_Bibliothek\">Johannes a Lasco Bibliothek</a> (JALB)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">That leftmost nodes are always PV-nodes, does not imply each PV-node is leftmost - since we have to deal with real search trees rather than minimal ones.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=387518\">Re: simple node definitions question</a> post by <a href=\"/Robert_Hyatt\" title=\"Robert Hyatt\">Robert Hyatt</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 13, 2004</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/Ernst_A._Heinz\" title=\"Ernst A. Heinz\">Ernst A. Heinz</a> (<b>1998</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://people.csail.mit.edu/heinz/dt/node18.html\">Extended Futility Pruning</a>.</i> <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#21_2\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 21, No. 2</a>, pp. 75-83</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/Search\" title=\"Search\">Up one Level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260228163725\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.069 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.635 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 103/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 194/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key oscar70_mw1-mw_:pcache:idhash:931-0!canonical and timestamp 20260228163724 and revision id 20072\n -->\n"
